<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
  <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 text-center mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 group"><summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer text-slate-900 list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">How accurate are these financial calculators?<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 shrink-0 transition group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg></summary><p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">They provide practical planning estimates using common 2026 assumptions for taxes, debt, savings, and digital nomad costs. Your real numbers may vary based on state rules, lender terms, credits, and personal circumstances.</p></details>
    <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 group"><summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer text-slate-900 list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">Are these tools suitable for gig workers and freelancers?<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 shrink-0 transition group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg></summary><p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes. The Gig Tax Optimizer is designed as a 2026 gig economy tax calculator for freelancers, rideshare drivers, delivery couriers, and creators who need to estimate self-employment tax and quarterly payments.</p></details>
    <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 group"><summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer text-slate-900 list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">Can I compare cities before becoming a digital nomad?<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 shrink-0 transition group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg></summary><p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes. Use the Cost of Living Comparison tool alongside the Digital Nomad Calculator to compare monthly living costs, one-time setup fees, and your likely break-even timeline.</p></details>
    <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 group"><summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer text-slate-900 list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">How do I know if I might become tax resident abroad?<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 shrink-0 transition group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg></summary><p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The Tax Residency Checker highlights common risk signals like spending more than 183 days in a country, losing your tax home, or maintaining a permanent home abroad.</p></details>
    <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 group"><summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer text-slate-900 list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">What is the best order to use the nomad tools?<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 shrink-0 transition group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg></summary><p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">A strong workflow is Digital Nomad Calculator → Cost of Living Comparison → Break-Even Savings Calculator → Tax Residency Checker → Nomad Health Insurance Estimator.</p></details>
    <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 group"><summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer text-slate-900 list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4">Do PDF export and email sharing work on all calculator pages?<svg class="w-4 h-4 text-slate-400 shrink-0 transition group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg></summary><p class="mt-3 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes. Every standalone calculator page includes PDF export, email sharing, and social sharing so you can save or send results quickly.</p></details>
